────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
ADDITIONAL DISCLAIMER FOR ONEDRIVE NUKE
────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

This software performs DESTRUCTIVE operations on a Windows system, including:

  - Permanent deletion of files, folders, and user data associated with
    Microsoft OneDrive.
  - Removal of Windows scheduled tasks and services related to OneDrive.
  - Modification of OneDrive's own Group Policy registry key and
    Software Restriction Policy registry keys.
  - Installation of Image File Execution Options (IFEO) debugger hijacks that
    block execution of specific OneDrive binaries.

This software is scoped to affect Microsoft OneDrive only. While every effort
has been made to confine all changes strictly to OneDrive-related files,
processes, and registry keys (see the README's "Scope Guarantee" section),
you are responsible for reviewing the source code before running it on any
system you do not fully control.

By using this software, you acknowledge that:

  - You are responsible for backing up any data you wish to preserve, including
    files synced via OneDrive, before running the script.
  - The author and contributors are not liable for any data loss, system
    instability, or service interruption resulting from use of this software.
  - You should review the source code before executing it, especially when
    using the `irm | iex` one-liner pattern.
